100
00:05:45,932 --> 00:05:47,433
I had no idea.

101
00:05:47,517 --> 00:05:48,893
You too, right?

102
00:05:50,311 --> 00:05:53,481
-What if Ko Hyeong-su didn't believe her?
-I'm sure he did.

103
00:05:53,564 --> 00:05:54,607
She even fooled us.

104
00:05:55,274 --> 00:05:56,776
You had no idea, right?

105
00:05:56,859 --> 00:06:00,822
I was worried that weasel would catch on,
so I had to do a test run.

106
00:06:00,905 --> 00:06:02,824
It was so nerve-racking.

107
00:06:03,699 --> 00:06:06,619
There are no cabs here
because of the protest. Let's walk a bit.

108
00:06:06,702 --> 00:06:07,537
I have to go.

109
00:06:07,620 --> 00:06:08,579
Professor.

110
00:06:09,205 --> 00:06:10,039
I'm starving.

111
00:06:11,958 --> 00:06:13,167
Professor!

112
00:06:14,877 --> 00:06:16,254
I did a good job, you know.

113
00:06:17,505 --> 00:06:18,923
Can we grab a bite to eat?

114
00:06:20,174 --> 00:06:22,009
I told you I never eat with my students…

115
00:06:23,136 --> 00:06:23,970
I'm Kang Dan.

116
00:06:36,149 --> 00:06:37,859
PROSECUTOR JIN HYEONG-U

117
00:06:40,778 --> 00:06:41,946
Search and seizure?

118
00:06:42,905 --> 00:06:46,409
-What did you tell Prosecutor Lee--
-Not all prosecutors are like you.

119
00:06:46,492 --> 00:06:49,078
Are you trying to get
Prosecutor Lee fired?

120
00:06:49,829 --> 00:06:51,581
Can you afford to worry about him now?

121
00:06:52,165 --> 00:06:55,168
I heard your number was found
on the burner phone they seized.

122
00:06:55,793 --> 00:06:59,630
Please cooperate with the investigation.
I'm eating now. I have to go.

123
00:07:05,761 --> 00:07:07,180
Can I just eat without this?

124
00:07:13,144 --> 00:07:15,646
Want to hear about the best jjajangmyeon
I've ever had?

125
00:07:16,397 --> 00:07:20,193
The jjajangmyeon I had in your office
when you were a prosecutor.

126
00:07:20,276 --> 00:07:22,820
My gosh, it was so good.

127
00:07:23,446 --> 00:07:26,365
I can't believe I was that hungry
after causing such trouble.

128
00:07:28,242 --> 00:07:30,453
I have to say,
the portion here is quite small.

129
00:07:31,704 --> 00:07:34,081
Maybe I should've ordered the jumbo size.

130
00:07:35,625 --> 00:07:37,126
If you're done, let's get going.

131
00:07:45,635 --> 00:07:46,552
You know, the law…

132
00:07:49,055 --> 00:07:51,390
The law that I'm studying with you.

133
00:07:55,686 --> 00:07:58,189
It'll punish Ko Hyeong-su
for what he did, right?

134
00:08:08,199 --> 00:08:10,618
Are you telling me to destroy evidence?

135
00:08:14,705 --> 00:08:17,041
There's no need to spell it out.

136
00:08:17,917 --> 00:08:23,589
It's just that no one can drag us into it
without the burner phone.

137
00:08:24,549 --> 00:08:27,385
Do whatever it takes to get rid of it.

138
00:08:30,137 --> 00:08:32,223
We're in the same boat, you know?

139
00:08:34,058 --> 00:08:36,644
Then you shouldn't have kept anything
from me--

140
00:08:36,727 --> 00:08:38,563
I told you. I never meant to lie to you.

141
00:08:38,646 --> 00:08:41,899
I just didn't tell you
because you didn't need to know.

142
00:08:43,526 --> 00:08:45,403
At times like this,

143
00:08:45,486 --> 00:08:48,573
you need to hang tight and help me out.

144
00:08:51,659 --> 00:08:52,743
According to Jin,

145
00:08:52,827 --> 00:08:55,496
he met Ko when he was stationed
in the National Assembly.

146
00:08:55,580 --> 00:08:58,416
He admitted speaking to Ko on the phone
a few times recently.

147
00:08:58,499 --> 00:09:02,837
But apparently, it was regarding
the constitutional review.

148
00:09:02,920 --> 00:09:04,589
What do I say to that?

149
00:09:04,672 --> 00:09:07,592
-They only talked? No text messages?
-No, just phone calls.

150
00:09:07,675 --> 00:09:10,219
We had an analysis done
to see if anything was deleted,

151
00:09:10,303 --> 00:09:11,387
but no text messages.

152
00:09:12,221 --> 00:09:14,223
But according to the phone records,

153
00:09:14,307 --> 00:09:17,602
he only used the burner phone to talk
to Choi Jae-cheol and Jin Hyeong-u.

154
00:09:17,685 --> 00:09:18,853
He's hiding something.

155
00:09:18,936 --> 00:09:21,439
That's enough
to make Prosecutor Jin feel cornered.

156
00:09:21,522 --> 00:09:26,527
The fact that we caught Assemblyman Ko
talking to Choi Jae-cheol on the phone

157
00:09:26,611 --> 00:09:29,030
can prove the interference with business

158
00:09:29,113 --> 00:09:31,657
but not the incitement
to commit the murder,

159
00:09:31,741 --> 00:09:35,077
which means we need Ki Du-seong
or Choi Jae-cheol's confession.

160
00:09:35,161 --> 00:09:36,912
Ki will spill the truth soon.

161
00:09:45,588 --> 00:09:48,716
You should tell the police
what you heard from Ki Du-seong

162
00:09:48,799 --> 00:09:50,468
before he spills the truth.

163
00:09:54,347 --> 00:09:57,433
Why take a risk? You know the police
searched and seized Ko's office.

164
00:09:57,516 --> 00:10:00,394
The court won't support
Ki's self-defense argument.

165
00:10:00,478 --> 00:10:01,812
And if that happens,

166
00:10:01,896 --> 00:10:05,149
Ki certainly won't keep his mouth shut
for Ko. You know that.

167
00:10:12,198 --> 00:10:15,117
It's time you let go of the rotten rope.

168
00:10:27,672 --> 00:10:29,674
VOICE MEMO

169
00:10:39,517 --> 00:10:40,768
Murder?

170
00:10:40,851 --> 00:10:42,228
You really had no idea.

171
00:10:42,895 --> 00:10:46,232
You would've been found dead in that room
had you known about it.

172
00:10:55,282 --> 00:10:58,202
While investigating the suspicion
that Assemblyman Ko Hyeong-su

173
00:10:58,285 --> 00:11:00,830
had ordered Ki Du-seong to murder Yang,
a law professor,

174
00:11:00,913 --> 00:11:01,914
we raided a site

175
00:11:01,997 --> 00:11:05,626
where comments were being manipulated
systematically under his command,

176
00:11:05,709 --> 00:11:09,046
so we got a warrant issued
and searched his office.

177
00:11:09,130 --> 00:11:11,424
I have huge respect
for Prof. Yang and Prof. Kim.

178
00:11:11,507 --> 00:11:13,843
Seriously, talk about perfect teamwork.

179
00:11:13,926 --> 00:11:15,845
Prof. Kim, by publicly alleging facts.

180
00:11:15,928 --> 00:11:19,265
Prof. Yang, by publicizing
the allegations. They got him good.

181
00:11:19,348 --> 00:11:21,350
Wow, who knew this was their plan?

182
00:11:21,434 --> 00:11:25,980
Yangcrates did this to make sure
they'd properly investigate Ko Hyeong-su.

183
00:11:26,063 --> 00:11:27,773
Yes, people need to know

184
00:11:27,857 --> 00:11:30,693
why the future presidential candidate
is being investigated.

185
00:11:30,776 --> 00:11:33,737
Ko Hyeong-su proposed the bill
and toyed with us.

186
00:11:33,821 --> 00:11:35,990
I bet he didn't see this coming.

187
00:11:36,073 --> 00:11:37,825
He dug his own grave.

188
00:11:37,908 --> 00:11:39,535
Don't be too excited.

189
00:11:39,618 --> 00:11:42,621
We don't know who will be buried
in the grave that Ko has dug.

190
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:48,836
Despite the trouble that my son caused,

191
00:11:50,796 --> 00:11:53,549
my approval rating
has been steadily going up,

192
00:11:54,216 --> 00:11:57,052
and some people
are determined to bring me down.

193
00:11:57,136 --> 00:12:02,057
It is truly unfortunate that the police
and Professor Yang Jong-hoon

194
00:12:03,934 --> 00:12:07,062
are letting those people use them
to get what they want.

195
00:12:07,146 --> 00:12:09,523
Launching a counterattack
right after the briefing.

196
00:12:09,607 --> 00:12:11,567
He wouldn't just sit back and do nothing.

197
00:12:11,650 --> 00:12:13,903
But the fact that
the court issued the warrant

198
00:12:13,986 --> 00:12:16,071
must mean there's substantial evidence.

199
00:12:16,155 --> 00:12:17,573
Evidence, my foot.

200
00:12:17,656 --> 00:12:20,784
The judge who issued the warrant.
Guess who his niece is.

201
00:12:20,868 --> 00:12:22,703
ASSEMBLYMAN KO HYEONG-SU
PRESS CONFERENCE

202
00:12:22,786 --> 00:12:23,621
She is…

203
00:12:24,705 --> 00:12:26,540
one of Yang Jong-hoon's students.

204
00:12:36,091 --> 00:12:37,843
LETTER OF APOLOGY

205
00:12:37,927 --> 00:12:39,762
So, after reading this letter,

206
00:12:39,845 --> 00:12:41,972
you feel torn about whether to ask them

207
00:12:42,056 --> 00:12:43,641
not to punish him?

208
00:12:44,808 --> 00:12:49,146
He wrote this with his blood
and promised me that he won't do it again.

209
00:12:49,230 --> 00:12:50,105
LETTER OF APOLOGY

210
00:12:50,189 --> 00:12:53,234
"I should've been patient
even when you were getting on my nerves.

211
00:12:53,317 --> 00:12:55,819
I'm really sorry
I lost my temper and hit you."

212
00:12:57,321 --> 00:13:00,574
This is not what I'd expect
from someone who's genuinely sorry.

213
00:13:00,658 --> 00:13:02,952
He should not have hit you,
no matter what.

214
00:13:03,035 --> 00:13:06,247
But if I never got on his nerves…

215
00:13:06,872 --> 00:13:09,291
You said what got on his nerves
was the fact that

216
00:13:09,833 --> 00:13:12,169
you kept the job
which he had told you to quit.

217
00:13:13,837 --> 00:13:16,257
He didn't like that
the cafe was owned by a guy,

218
00:13:16,757 --> 00:13:18,008
so he told me to quit.

219
00:13:18,884 --> 00:13:21,637
But I needed the job.

220
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:23,681
That's not your fault, Seong-hui.

221
00:13:24,723 --> 00:13:27,726
"I'll never hit you again,
no matter what you do."

222
00:13:27,810 --> 00:13:29,228
This is like him saying,

223
00:13:29,311 --> 00:13:33,399
"You're at fault, but I do apologize
for not being understanding enough."

224
00:13:34,441 --> 00:13:36,902
"We should've both been careful."

225
00:13:36,986 --> 00:13:39,488
I have no idea why you think
he actually feels bad.

226
00:13:39,572 --> 00:13:41,323
I think he's practically saying

227
00:13:41,407 --> 00:13:45,035
he'll keep hitting you
if you don't change your ways.

228
00:13:45,119 --> 00:13:46,328
But…

229
00:13:47,788 --> 00:13:49,248
he wrote this with his blood.

230
00:13:49,331 --> 00:13:50,749
I interpret that as…

231
00:13:51,834 --> 00:13:54,169
"Blood will be shed
if you don't listen to me.

232
00:13:55,004 --> 00:13:57,548
I'll teach you a lesson."
This looks like a threat to me.

233
00:13:59,425 --> 00:14:01,635
Then what do I do?

234
00:14:13,772 --> 00:14:15,190
Seong-hui, you're not alone.

235
00:14:17,735 --> 00:14:19,486
Let's find a way.

236
00:14:24,617 --> 00:14:25,743
NOTICE BOARD

237
00:14:25,826 --> 00:14:26,911
PRELIMINARY RESULTS

238
00:14:27,411 --> 00:14:28,829
No!

239
00:14:28,913 --> 00:14:31,916
What if we didn't pass
because of the draft I wrote?

240
00:14:31,999 --> 00:14:34,335
I told you to revise the whole thing!

241
00:14:39,715 --> 00:14:41,759
No! Don't show me.

242
00:14:41,842 --> 00:14:44,803
-What? 351824! 351824, right?
-Yes!

243
00:14:44,887 --> 00:14:46,096
Yes!

244
00:14:46,180 --> 00:14:47,139
Congratulations!

245
00:14:47,222 --> 00:14:48,641
Yours is 297632, right?

246
00:14:48,724 --> 00:14:50,267
Yeah, do you see it?

247
00:14:50,893 --> 00:14:51,810
Of course.

248
00:14:51,894 --> 00:14:54,188
Nice! We're moving on to the semifinals!

249
00:14:54,897 --> 00:14:56,523
See? I'm not a nuisance, right?

250
00:14:56,607 --> 00:14:57,858
Let's check the question.

251
00:14:57,942 --> 00:14:59,568
Right, for the semifinals.

252
00:14:59,652 --> 00:15:00,903
Let's see.

