771
00:46:13,774 --> 00:46:16,235
and that she be sentenced to three years.

772
00:46:16,860 --> 00:46:19,154
Thank you for your closing argument.

773
00:46:19,905 --> 00:46:22,658
He's very good.
Too bad they got the penalty points.

774
00:46:24,201 --> 00:46:26,286
Defense,
please share your closing argument.

775
00:46:30,958 --> 00:46:32,459
Why not stay until the end?

776
00:46:32,543 --> 00:46:35,629
JUSTICE MOCK TRIAL COMPETITION
CRIMINAL TRIAL

777
00:46:35,712 --> 00:46:36,964
The prosecutors argue that

778
00:46:37,047 --> 00:46:40,509
the defendant's abandonment of the victim
resulted in her death.

779
00:46:40,592 --> 00:46:42,678
But it is not convincing enough.

780
00:46:42,761 --> 00:46:45,389
Despite the prejudice
against single mothers,

781
00:46:45,472 --> 00:46:47,975
-she did her best to raise her child.
-She did her best.

782
00:46:48,058 --> 00:46:50,852
Because it's rare to die
after getting a vaccine--

783
00:46:50,936 --> 00:46:52,312
That's my section.

784
00:46:52,396 --> 00:46:54,940
I know, but it won't hurt
to have it all memorized.

785
00:46:56,608 --> 00:46:59,111
The defendant was worried about her child,

786
00:46:59,194 --> 00:47:03,031
but she had to go to work
to support herself and her child…

787
00:47:04,283 --> 00:47:05,867
We're moving on to the finals.

788
00:47:05,951 --> 00:47:07,578
Let's become the final winner.

789
00:47:07,661 --> 00:47:08,495
Let's do it!

790
00:47:08,579 --> 00:47:09,830
MOCK TRIAL COMPETITION

791
00:47:09,913 --> 00:47:12,541
Oh, did you guys lose?

792
00:47:17,879 --> 00:47:19,590
How did the trial go?

793
00:47:19,673 --> 00:47:21,842
He should've been arrested
in the courtroom,

794
00:47:21,925 --> 00:47:23,427
but he'll end up in jail soon.

795
00:47:23,510 --> 00:47:24,344
-Yes!
-Nice!

796
00:47:25,762 --> 00:47:26,680
MOM

797
00:47:27,806 --> 00:47:28,807
MOM

798
00:47:30,892 --> 00:47:31,727
Let's go.

799
00:47:37,733 --> 00:47:39,067
Hey, Byeol.

800
00:47:39,651 --> 00:47:40,902
Where's Dan?

801
00:47:43,739 --> 00:47:44,948
You're at the airport?

802
00:47:45,032 --> 00:47:47,576
Yeah, I saw Mom and Byeol.

803
00:47:47,659 --> 00:47:49,786
I had to make time to fly here
for the trial.

804
00:47:50,412 --> 00:47:52,497
I barely got to see you.

805
00:47:54,041 --> 00:47:55,292
You'll be a good lawyer.

806
00:47:58,920 --> 00:47:59,921
Thanks.

807
00:48:00,672 --> 00:48:02,007
I should thank you.

808
00:48:02,090 --> 00:48:03,925
Thanks to you, I can go back worry-free.

809
00:48:04,968 --> 00:48:07,054
ASSEMBLYMENT KO HYEONG-SU FOUND GUILTY

810
00:48:07,137 --> 00:48:08,096
All right.

811
00:48:09,097 --> 00:48:10,098
Have a safe flight.

812
00:48:19,983 --> 00:48:20,901
You did a good job.

813
00:48:20,984 --> 00:48:22,611
Good job, my foot.

814
00:48:23,195 --> 00:48:27,741
You won't settle with Attorney Song
because of the constitutional appeal.

815
00:48:27,824 --> 00:48:32,454
He said he'd make me a partner
at Hyeongseol if I helped him with it.

816
00:48:32,537 --> 00:48:35,707
I'll give you the professor position
at the Legal Clinic.

817
00:48:35,791 --> 00:48:37,334
No, thanks. It'll pay peanuts.

818
00:48:37,417 --> 00:48:38,919
I really didn't want to do it.

819
00:48:40,420 --> 00:48:41,630
How would you have felt?

820
00:48:41,713 --> 00:48:43,131
I really hated myself

821
00:48:43,882 --> 00:48:47,636
for handing over the bill
to abolish the law to Ko Hyeong-su.

822
00:48:48,178 --> 00:48:50,013
But thanks to it,

823
00:48:50,097 --> 00:48:53,308
you could help the Bad FaMa client
get acquitted.

824
00:48:53,392 --> 00:48:55,560
Well, no more.

825
00:48:56,269 --> 00:48:59,398
Why should I help Ko Hyeong-su
who uses the law for his own gain?

826
00:48:59,981 --> 00:49:01,733
Let's tackle this together.

827
00:49:02,401 --> 00:49:04,736
If we manage to get it declared
unconstitutional,

828
00:49:04,820 --> 00:49:07,447
we'll leave our mark
on the history of criminal law.

829
00:49:07,531 --> 00:49:09,282
Let's get started now.

830
00:49:10,492 --> 00:49:12,411
What? Start what?

831
00:49:12,494 --> 00:49:15,455
Are you the mastermind behind Prof. Yang?

832
00:49:16,415 --> 00:49:18,041
The mastermind behind Jong-hoon?

833
00:49:18,917 --> 00:49:20,919
We do have similar figures.

834
00:49:51,908 --> 00:49:54,494
PRETTY YE-SEUL:
JI-HO'S TEAM WON! CONGRATULATIONS!

835
00:50:09,426 --> 00:50:11,219
PUB

836
00:50:15,807 --> 00:50:16,725
Good job.

837
00:50:25,567 --> 00:50:27,152
-Congratulations!
-Congratulations!

838
00:50:27,235 --> 00:50:28,570
-Thanks!
-Congratulations!

839
00:50:28,653 --> 00:50:30,030
-Well done.
-Way to go!

840
00:50:30,113 --> 00:50:31,948
Winning is important,

841
00:50:32,032 --> 00:50:34,785
but kudos to you for not betraying
your conscience in court.

842
00:50:34,868 --> 00:50:38,497
-Agreed.
-She has such a refreshing outlook.

843
00:50:38,580 --> 00:50:41,291
But you guys made it to the semifinals.
You should've won.

844
00:50:41,374 --> 00:50:43,168
You couldn't even participate in it.

845
00:50:43,251 --> 00:50:45,212
I would've won had I participated in it.

846
00:50:45,295 --> 00:50:46,421
Even Bok-gi won.

847
00:50:46,505 --> 00:50:48,131
Why are you dragging me into this?

848
00:50:48,215 --> 00:50:49,716
You learned everything from me.

849
00:50:49,800 --> 00:50:51,885
The winners, tell us how you feel.

850
00:50:51,968 --> 00:50:52,803
Yes, tell us.

851
00:50:52,886 --> 00:50:54,262
-My gosh.
-Way to go!

852
00:50:54,346 --> 00:50:56,306
MOM

853
00:50:59,309 --> 00:51:00,185
What's up?

854
00:51:00,268 --> 00:51:03,271
Look at you.
You got eliminated in the semifinals.

855
00:51:03,355 --> 00:51:04,940
Because of your roommate--

856
00:51:05,023 --> 00:51:07,108
I really didn't want to do it
because of you,

857
00:51:07,192 --> 00:51:09,027
but my roommate convinced me to do it.

858
00:51:09,110 --> 00:51:11,613
And it's not her fault that we lost.

859
00:51:11,696 --> 00:51:12,906
Sol did a good job.

860
00:51:14,032 --> 00:51:15,367
So stop this, okay?

861
00:51:24,376 --> 00:51:25,627
Bottoms up.

862
00:51:41,351 --> 00:51:43,854
You said "Sol" did a good job. Is that me?

863
00:51:48,984 --> 00:51:50,193
It is me?

864
00:51:53,488 --> 00:51:55,782
My gosh, I'm so happy right now.

865
00:51:57,158 --> 00:51:58,368
Can you say it again?

866
00:51:58,451 --> 00:51:59,870
Call me "Sol."

867
00:51:59,953 --> 00:52:01,246
-Cut it out.
-Call me "sis."

868
00:52:02,497 --> 00:52:03,498
Sis.

869
00:52:05,166 --> 00:52:08,253
What are you doing here?
I thought you'd be all sad.

870
00:52:08,920 --> 00:52:10,255
I was sad that we didn't win.

871
00:52:11,214 --> 00:52:12,757
But my roomie said I did well.

872
00:52:14,342 --> 00:52:15,760
"Sol did a good job."

873
00:52:19,180 --> 00:52:21,558
I wouldn't be this happy even if we won.

874
00:52:21,641 --> 00:52:24,060
-You need to give me credit for it.
-No.

875
00:52:24,144 --> 00:52:25,520
You went overboard.

876
00:52:25,604 --> 00:52:27,105
What are you talking about?

877
00:52:27,188 --> 00:52:28,815
I think I did a pretty good job.

878
00:52:28,899 --> 00:52:31,151
I must say, I'm jealous that they won.

879
00:52:31,776 --> 00:52:33,028
We'll win next time.

880
00:52:47,083 --> 00:52:50,295
All right! Let's do it!

881
00:52:50,378 --> 00:52:53,048
Okay? Let's win!

882
00:52:54,799 --> 00:52:55,884
Go, team!

883
00:53:03,767 --> 00:53:05,852
"Every new time will give its law."

884
00:53:06,394 --> 00:53:08,021
Maxim Gorky.

885
00:53:08,104 --> 00:53:10,231
"Law is an ethical minimum."

886
00:53:10,315 --> 00:53:11,566
Georg Jellinek.

887
00:53:11,650 --> 00:53:16,655
"The law destroys
those who do not fear it."

888
00:53:18,073 --> 00:53:19,282
George Gordon Byron.

889
00:53:19,366 --> 00:53:21,201
"We are not machines.

890
00:53:21,284 --> 00:53:23,161
Abide by the Labor Standards Act."

891
00:53:24,079 --> 00:53:25,080
Jeon Tae-il.

892
00:53:26,122 --> 00:53:27,999
"An eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth."

893
00:53:28,083 --> 00:53:29,125
Hammurabi.

894
00:53:29,209 --> 00:53:30,794
Doesn't count! You're out, Ji-ho.

895
00:53:30,877 --> 00:53:31,795
Why?

896
00:53:32,462 --> 00:53:35,298
Hammurabi, seriously? That's too easy.

897
00:53:35,382 --> 00:53:37,092
What? This is not fair.

898
00:53:38,301 --> 00:53:39,928
"Judge fairly…

899
00:53:41,054 --> 00:53:43,390
and make sure no one suffers unjustly."

900
00:53:45,892 --> 00:53:46,893
Seo…

901
00:53:48,353 --> 00:53:50,855
Byung-ju.

902
00:54:25,849 --> 00:54:28,560
1 YEAR LATER

903
00:54:28,643 --> 00:54:31,062
The results of the constitutional review

904
00:54:31,146 --> 00:54:34,733
requested by Head Prosecutor Jin Hyeong-u

905
00:54:34,816 --> 00:54:36,526
will be announced shortly.

906
00:54:36,609 --> 00:54:41,031
Prosecutor Jin Hyeong-u
requested the constitutional review,

907
00:54:41,114 --> 00:54:44,117
arguing that
Article 126 of the Criminal Code

908
00:54:44,200 --> 00:54:47,579
infringes the freedom of speech
and the public's right to know.

909
00:54:47,662 --> 00:54:48,913
For the common good…

910
00:54:48,997 --> 00:54:50,665
We'll finally find out the decision.

911
00:54:53,043 --> 00:54:57,130
Even if it's declared constitutional
and the trial has to resume,

912
00:54:57,213 --> 00:54:59,090
I won't lose the trial--

913
00:54:59,174 --> 00:55:00,842
But you lost the civil suit.

914
00:55:02,469 --> 00:55:03,636
I went easy on you

915
00:55:03,720 --> 00:55:07,015
to express my deepest condolences
on the passing of your father.

916
00:55:07,098 --> 00:55:08,224
This will be different.

917
00:55:08,308 --> 00:55:09,559
It won't be any different.

918
00:55:10,393 --> 00:55:11,895
Because I won't go easy on you.

919
00:55:15,482 --> 00:55:18,568
Shouldn't you resent Cho Tae-yeong
more than me?

920
00:55:21,529 --> 00:55:24,616
Unlike you,
he does not represent the common good.

921
00:55:27,327 --> 00:55:28,912
Represent the common good…

922
00:55:29,537 --> 00:55:30,455
Fine.

923
00:55:31,247 --> 00:55:35,001
Then I shall do my duty
and catch Cho Tae-yeong for you.

924
00:55:35,710 --> 00:55:39,672
In return, you'll file a petition
if the trial resumes. What do you say?

925
00:55:41,925 --> 00:55:45,095
I'm giving you a chance
to grab the golden rope.

926
00:55:45,178 --> 00:55:46,096
"Golden rope"?

927
00:55:48,389 --> 00:55:50,809
A bale of straw at the most.

928
00:55:56,481 --> 00:55:59,818
CONSTITUTIONAL COURT

929
00:56:00,443 --> 00:56:01,778
A bale of straw?

930
00:56:07,325 --> 00:56:08,243
That was cute.

931
00:56:18,169 --> 00:56:22,173
Could you please make sure
my face doesn't look too big?

932
00:56:25,135 --> 00:56:26,219
Ready, go.

933
00:56:26,302 --> 00:56:29,055
Our students go through the inquiries

934
00:56:29,139 --> 00:56:31,599
that we receive here
at the Legal Clinic Center

935
00:56:31,683 --> 00:56:34,936
and assist the professor
who is here as an advisor.

936
00:56:35,019 --> 00:56:37,105
In addition to offering
legal consultations…

937
00:56:37,188 --> 00:56:39,816
I'm so glad to hear that
your surgery went well, ma'am.

938
00:56:39,899 --> 00:56:41,609
It was all because of money.

939
00:56:42,110 --> 00:56:44,946
I really wanted that jerk
to pay for what he did, but I couldn't.

940
00:56:48,741 --> 00:56:51,953
Gosh, it's tiring
to be the chief of the Legal Clinic.

941
00:56:52,036 --> 00:56:54,998
Oh, dear. That interview was exhausting.

942
00:56:55,081 --> 00:56:56,666
Don't cry.

943
00:56:56,749 --> 00:57:00,670
My professor will make your husband
fear the law.

944
00:57:02,172 --> 00:57:06,676
What? Me? If she's submitted a request
not to punish him, it's game over.

945
00:57:06,759 --> 00:57:08,428
We can still get him punished.

946
00:57:10,513 --> 00:57:12,140
For child abuse, not assault.

947
00:57:12,223 --> 00:57:14,017
But he didn't hit the kid.

948
00:57:14,100 --> 00:57:15,852
-Right, he didn't.
-So how?

949
00:57:16,686 --> 00:57:18,730
But the kid saw his dad hit his mom.

950
00:57:18,813 --> 00:57:20,648
He's seen it many times, in fact.

951
00:57:21,483 --> 00:57:24,402
It left a deep emotional scar on the kid.

952
00:57:25,403 --> 00:57:26,905
And here's a precedent

953
00:57:26,988 --> 00:57:28,990
where the perpetrator
of such emotional abuse

954
00:57:29,073 --> 00:57:30,408
was convicted of child abuse.

955
00:57:31,701 --> 00:57:34,496
Now, I just want you to pass the bar exam
on the first try.

956
00:57:35,747 --> 00:57:37,207
I should go study now.

957
00:57:38,500 --> 00:57:39,334
Bye.

958
00:57:40,877 --> 00:57:43,463
My, she's good.

959
00:57:46,966 --> 00:57:48,468
You know carbs make you sleepy.

960
00:57:49,219 --> 00:57:52,847
You're in your 3L year.
Cut down on sleep before the bar exam.

961
00:57:52,931 --> 00:57:55,308
Goodness. She's already sleep-deprived.

962
00:57:55,391 --> 00:57:56,476
What if she fails?

963
00:57:57,101 --> 00:57:59,687
-That will be so embarrassing--
-I won't fail the bar.

964
00:57:59,771 --> 00:58:01,147
I suffer from insomnia.

965
00:58:02,690 --> 00:58:04,400
Please prescribe some sleeping pills.

966
00:58:04,484 --> 00:58:08,905
I think it'd be better to help you
beat insomnia without sleeping pills.

967
00:58:08,988 --> 00:58:11,908
I noticed something important
while observing your conversation

968
00:58:11,991 --> 00:58:13,993
and the way you interact with each other.

969
00:58:14,953 --> 00:58:19,958
Ma'am, you still want to decide
what your daughter should eat.

970
00:58:20,458 --> 00:58:24,837
And, Sol, instead of just saying
you want to eat bread,

971
00:58:24,921 --> 00:58:28,466
you said, "I won't fail the bar exam,
so I can eat the bread."

972
00:58:28,550 --> 00:58:33,179
It tells me you can't directly express
your needs and wants.

973
00:58:33,263 --> 00:58:38,351
It reminds me of the way
little kids interact with their parents.

974
00:58:38,851 --> 00:58:40,353
I think all three of you

975
00:58:40,436 --> 00:58:43,565
should try to become more mature
in your parent-child relationship

976
00:58:43,648 --> 00:58:47,235
so you can be happier and freer.

977
00:58:53,658 --> 00:58:54,576
Joon-hwi.

978
00:58:55,285 --> 00:58:57,203
-Where are you going?
-I need to wind down.

979
00:59:05,420 --> 00:59:06,588
You wanted to wind down.

980
00:59:09,173 --> 00:59:11,009
Yeah, while watching the trial.

981
00:59:11,092 --> 00:59:12,010
ADMIN OFFICE

982
00:59:13,803 --> 00:59:15,054
Right.

983
00:59:15,138 --> 00:59:18,349
I've been too busy studying
that I didn't have time to come here.

984
00:59:18,433 --> 00:59:21,269
Well, I should wind down a little too.

985
00:59:24,522 --> 00:59:28,026
Your Honor, please have mercy on me.

986
00:59:29,068 --> 00:59:30,903
If my house goes to auction,

987
00:59:31,779 --> 00:59:33,406
my grandson and I

988
00:59:34,574 --> 00:59:36,993
will become homeless.

989
00:59:39,537 --> 00:59:41,164
Are you willing to settle the case?

990
00:59:41,247 --> 00:59:42,915
The defendant seems to be in a bind.

991
00:59:43,541 --> 00:59:44,876
No, Your Honor.

992
00:59:44,959 --> 00:59:46,294
Please announce the decision.

993
00:59:47,962 --> 00:59:49,589
Please have mercy on me.

994
00:59:50,590 --> 00:59:52,675
I'll die soon anyway,

995
00:59:53,926 --> 00:59:56,846
but my poor grandson…

996
00:59:57,555 --> 01:00:01,768
We can't help you
if you just keep asking for mercy.

997
01:00:02,477 --> 01:00:03,478
Defendant.

998
01:00:04,145 --> 01:00:05,647
Instead of struggling alone,

999
01:00:05,730 --> 01:00:08,650
I suggest you ask an attorney
to go through the documents.

1000
01:00:09,651 --> 01:00:10,860
Your Honor.

1001
01:00:13,363 --> 01:00:16,199
I think he needs some time
to regain his composure.

1002
01:00:16,282 --> 01:00:17,533
Can we take a recess?

1003
01:00:21,120 --> 01:00:25,124
Seun Savings, the plaintiff,
loaned 20 million won to your son,

1004
01:00:25,208 --> 01:00:27,293
and you stood surety for him.

1005
01:00:28,002 --> 01:00:28,920
Yes.

1006
01:00:29,003 --> 01:00:33,216
Seun Savings loaned him the money
six years ago.

1007
01:00:34,050 --> 01:00:36,719
He died in a car accident
five years and four months ago

1008
01:00:36,803 --> 01:00:38,262
while just paying the interest.

1009
01:00:38,346 --> 01:00:40,848
And the interest grew larger
than the principal,

1010
01:00:40,932 --> 01:00:43,184
so the total amount
is now over 50 million won.

1011
01:00:43,267 --> 01:00:44,435
Right.

1012
01:00:44,519 --> 01:00:49,148
The plaintiff is asking for the money back
after keeping quiet all these years.

1013
01:00:50,525 --> 01:00:53,528
Begging the judge in tears
won't solve the problem.

1014
01:00:54,654 --> 01:00:56,280
When the trial resumes,

1015
01:00:56,364 --> 01:00:59,158
just say this one thing to the judge.

1016
01:00:59,242 --> 01:01:00,493
Pardon me?

1017
01:01:00,576 --> 01:01:01,994
Please repeat after me.

1018
01:01:02,870 --> 01:01:04,372
The statute of limitations…

1019
01:01:05,415 --> 01:01:07,500
The statute of limitations…

1020
01:01:07,583 --> 01:01:10,420
on the loan has already expired.

1021
01:01:10,503 --> 01:01:14,424
on the loan has already expired.

1022
01:01:17,009 --> 01:01:18,386
I have the draft ready.

1023
01:01:19,387 --> 01:01:22,223
This loan is considered commercial debt.

1024
01:01:22,306 --> 01:01:25,643
So, as of November 26th, 2021, the date
the plaintiff filed the complaint,

1025
01:01:25,727 --> 01:01:29,480
the statute of limitations of five years
on this loan

1026
01:01:29,564 --> 01:01:31,357
has already expired.

1027
01:01:31,441 --> 01:01:34,152
Ergo, the plaintiff's request
should be denied.

1028
01:01:35,027 --> 01:01:37,864
LAW AND ORDER THAT PUT PEOPLE FIRST

1029
01:01:40,408 --> 01:01:41,617
Why are you here?

1030
01:01:44,829 --> 01:01:46,330
Was that a gift?

1031
01:01:48,624 --> 01:01:51,461
Are you still going on
about the lot I gave to Byung-ju?

1032
01:01:53,045 --> 01:01:56,382
You want to hear me say
that it was a bribe?

1033
01:01:58,468 --> 01:02:01,679
What will change if I admit to it now?

1034
01:02:03,139 --> 01:02:05,224
Prohibition against double jeopardy,
you know?

1035
01:02:07,935 --> 01:02:11,773
It'll only make you beat yourself up more
for failing to solve it.

1036
01:02:47,934 --> 01:02:49,143
It was a bribe, wasn't it?

1037
01:02:52,313 --> 01:02:54,065
I showed everyone that…

1038
01:02:56,484 --> 01:02:57,777
the law is not just.

1039
01:03:01,155 --> 01:03:02,490
That I was wrong.

1040
01:03:12,834 --> 01:03:15,920
What will change if I admit to it now?

1041
01:03:17,839 --> 01:03:21,676
It'll only make you beat yourself up more
for failing to solve it.

1042
01:03:24,804 --> 01:03:27,014
Because I have students

1043
01:03:28,099 --> 01:03:29,517
who learn from it…

1044
01:04:27,366 --> 01:04:29,577
I'm Yang Jong-hoon,
your criminal law professor.

1045
01:04:32,163 --> 01:04:37,919
A FEW YEARS LATER

1046
01:04:42,214 --> 01:04:45,092
KANG SOL
ATTORNEY AT LAW

1047
01:04:49,597 --> 01:04:53,935
Just bring these documents next time,

1048
01:04:54,018 --> 01:04:56,020
and I'll go over them for you.

1049
01:04:56,103 --> 01:04:57,688
LAW OFFICE KANG &amp; PARK

1050
01:04:59,148 --> 01:05:01,233
I'm sorry. Something's come up.

1051
01:05:02,193 --> 01:05:05,029
As Mr. Park helped you originally,
he'll do the rest for you.

1052
01:05:06,322 --> 01:05:08,157
Mr. Park, can you take care of the rest?

1053
01:05:09,241 --> 01:05:10,076
Sure.

1054
01:05:14,455 --> 01:05:17,959
How can I help you…

1055
01:05:24,340 --> 01:05:26,884
PROSECUTOR HAN JOON-HWI

1056
01:05:53,035 --> 01:05:54,787
The law is imperfect justice.

1057
01:05:56,998 --> 01:06:01,252
But when you teach law,
the law must be perfect.

1058
01:06:07,842 --> 01:06:11,220
And when you study law,
it must be synonymous with justice.

1059
01:06:14,140 --> 01:06:17,768
Because unjust law
is the most cruel violence.

